{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 2 introduces a taxonomy of attacks in adversarial machine learning for GenAI systems.",
    "Similar to the PredAI taxonomy in Figure 1, this taxonomy is frst categorized by the attacker's objectives, which include availability breakdowns, integrity violations, and privacy compromise.",
    "For GenAI systems, violations of abuse are also especially relevant.",
    "The capabilities that an adversary must leverage to achieve their objectives are shown in the outer layer of the objective circles.",
    "Attack classes are shown as callouts connected to the capabilities required to mount each attack."
  ]
}